Comments: Columns H,I are scaled per 50 plants
For Aborney, Calavi, and Hunkpogon, total bugs is per 2m row, with plants every 0.25m
For Paouignan, total bugs is per 2m row, rows are an average of 32m, with plants an average of every 0.325m
Sowing assumed to be on May 16 (panel A) and Sept 1 (panels B,C)
A (column J) is scaled by 16 to better convert from adults per row for model fitting
